{"name": "Music - Guitar", "id": 236, "content": "<p><a href=\"http://satyendra.website/#/article/254\" target=\"_blank\">Song Analysis</a>, <a href=\"http://satyendra.website/#/article/255\" target=\"_blank\">Music Composition</a>, <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1ohhjzWCfFO8-Dz-y5lbbDdzC8Jsu3VdPTJvtvADc5Mk/edit#gid=0\" target=\"_blank\">Practice Diary</a>, <a href=\"https://www.thisisclassicalguitar.com/20-favorite-exercises-for-classical-guitar/\" target=\"_blank\">Exercises</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Music is composed of Tension &amp; Release. Start somewhere, build tension, slowly release. It&#39;s also about patterns. Pattern of intervals/gaps, pattern of pitch, pattern of leap, pattern of pattern, ...</p>\n\n<p>Musicality also comes from variation &amp; contrast: <strong>Low and high, Slow and Fast, Sound and Silence, Bright and Dark, Emotion and Dullness, a sense of Progression &amp; Stability, Consonace &amp; Dissonance, ...</strong></p>\n\n<p>Tonal music means the song is centered around particular tone(s). Atonal has wide range of tones, and is not centered rather distributed over tones.</p>\n\n<p>Songs are based on Melody + Harmony + Tone Color + Rythm. (Melody itself requires Rythm and Tone Color). <em>Ornamentation, Licks &amp; Riffs add some spice to the song.</em></p>\n\n<p>Tool&nbsp;for chord identification:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.oolimo.de/gitarrenakkorde/analysieren\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.oolimo.de/gitarrenakkorde/analysieren</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.8notes.com/all/classical/sheet_music/?difficulty=2\" target=\"_blank\">Sheets/Tabs</a>&nbsp; <a href=\"https://blog.landr.com/music-symbols/\" target=\"_blank\">Music Symbols</a> <a href=\"https://scalesandarpeggios.com/the-big-list-of-music-theory-terms-and-definitions/\" target=\"_blank\">Music Terms</a>&nbsp; <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4QopYciKsUA&amp;list=PLDNPXoSAAaRJ0Uv2qG8_6G-rzwSJzxSRd&amp;index=14\" target=\"_blank\">Reading Music</a></p>\n\n<p>Etudes:</p>\n\n<p>Beginner to Intermediate: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0gzZ2-efo3s&amp;list=PLVzwBH6y7aM4gMb6_YXJjVoE6-Mh-mAWA\" target=\"_blank\">Sor Op60</a>, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t9EJ3wTE8cU\" target=\"_blank\">Sor Op44</a>,&nbsp; <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=68-zYu97Uoo&amp;t=315s\" target=\"_blank\">24 Preludes by Domeniconi</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=atxVSMbI_bo&amp;list=PLVzwBH6y7aM47GB10nW836SMtTl-HNf3h\">Giuliani Op50</a></p>\n\n<p>Intermediate to Advanced: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kl-6-Rqj3FA\" target=\"_blank\">Sor Op35</a>, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8DrGpKrmMK4&amp;t=7s\" target=\"_blank\">SorOp31</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HP9y6l511UY&amp;list=PLVzwBH6y7aM7ygHyFimEIfGdkYAt7FJu4\">Brouwer</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Advanced: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-vpqzz_eKQk&amp;list=PLPJfhKFNvKSnyh0VqYAFyao4LV0LkBGWM\" target=\"_blank\">Sor Op6</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0KOkJDxcB9Q&amp;list=PL_XEHkKsriQi4-ZiYehZipsOGkiUt1Zel\" target=\"_blank\">Sor Op29</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.atrafana.com/beginners.html\">Flamenco Guitar Beginner</a></p>\n\n<p>Rythm Practice <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zy0E3LzWTwY\">[1] Swing</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WbultyEVOqw\">[2] Syncopation</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eMS2E1cl990\">[3] Syncopation Exercises</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sWcfdKTLn2c\">[4] Writing syncopation rhythm</a> []&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Understanding Chords and Harmony:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>(Bach&#39;s harmonic elaboration <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Wu0PPnUx34o\">[1] Elaboration</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7wkXZNxJfJY\">[2] Supensions</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d6UAKUpi82M\">[3] Decoration</a>&nbsp; )</li>\n\t<li>(Harmonic framework <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gMeJMqpd4zI\">[