pan></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"color:#8e44ad;\"><span style=\"font-style:normal;\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal;\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight:300;\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal;\"><span style=\"orphans:2;\"><span style=\"text-transform:none;\"><span style=\"widows:2;\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial;\"><strong>0 2 2 2 2 2 2\n</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"color:#6d6d6d\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:300\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\">\nWhole-Half Diminished =<font color=\"#179cd8\"><font style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"> 1 2 b3 4 b5 b6 6 7</font></font> (C D Eb F Gb Ab A B) - </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"color:#8e44ad;\"><span style=\"font-style:normal;\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal;\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight:300;\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal;\"><span style=\"orphans:2;\"><span style=\"text-transform:none;\"><span style=\"widows:2;\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial;\"><strong>0 2 1 2 1 2 1 2 1\n</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"color:#6d6d6d\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:300\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\">\nHalf-Whole Diminished =<font color=\"#179cd8\"><font style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"> 1 b2 b3 3 b5 5 6 b7</font></font> (C Db Eb E F# G A Bb) - </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"color:#8e44ad;\"><span style=\"font-style:normal;\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal;\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight:300;\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal;\"><span style=\"orphans:2;\"><span style=\"text-transform:none;\"><span style=\"widows:2;\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial;\"><strong>0 1 2 1 2 1 2 1 2</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></pre>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<h1 id=\"music-youtube\">Chords:</h1>\n\n<p>Major Chord Shapes: (Root&nbsp;&mdash; <strong>3 steps</strong> gap - Perfect 3<sup>rd</sup> &mdash; <strong>2 steps</strong> gap - Perfect 5<sup>th</sup>)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Minor Chord Shapes: (Root&nbsp;&mdash; <strong>2 steps</strong> gap - Perfect 3<sup>rd</sup> &mdash; <strong>3 steps</strong> gap - Perfect 5<sup>th</sup>)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Dominant 7<sup>th</sup> Chord Shapes: (Root&nbsp;&mdash; <strong>3 steps</strong> gap - Perfect 3<sup>rd</sup> &mdash; <strong>2 steps</strong> gap - Perfect 5<sup>th</sup> &mdash; <strong>2 steps</strong> gap - flat 7<sup>th</sup> )</p>\n\n<p>For Maj7th it will be 7th instead of flat-7th</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Augmented Chord Shapes: (Root&nbsp;&mdash; <strong>3 steps</strong> gap - Perfect 3<sup>rd</sup> &mdash; <strong>3 steps</strong> gap - Perfect 5<sup>th</sup> sharp)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Diminished Chord Shapes: (Root&nbsp;&mdash; <strong>2 steps</strong> gap - Perfect 3<sup>rd</sup> flat &mdash; <strong>2 steps</strong> gap - Perfect 5<sup>th</sup> flat)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Triads:</p>\n\n<p>On 3-higher-strings: Inversions: A-shape (first inversion), E-shape (second inversion), D-shape (third inversion)</p>\n\n<p><u>Key of Am:</u></p>\n\n<p>Am -&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Dm -&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Em -&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Chords that go well together:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Primary - Am, Dm, E, E7&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Secondary - C, B7, A7</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Chord Progressions:</strong></p>\n\n<p>1 5 4 1 4 6 2 3 2 6 ...</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>4, 5, 7 to create tension; 2, 3, 6 slow down tension; 1/8 to release..</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Circle of Fifths:</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/circle-of-fifths-zapista-ou.jpeg\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 500px;\" /></p>\n\n<hr />\n<h2>Voice Leading</h2>\n\n<p>Voice Leading:<br />\nDiatonic&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Seventh Chords:<br />\n1-(3-)7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Major7th<br />\n1-(3-)7b&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dom7th<br />\n1-3b-7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MajMin7th<br />\n1-3b-7b&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Min7th<br />\n1-3b-5b-7b&nbsp; Min7th 5b<br />\n1-3-5#-7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maj7th 5#<br />\n1-3b-5b-7b&nbsp; Dim7th</p>\n\n<p>3 Tonal Areas (Western Music): Tonic, Subdominant, Dominant<br />\n---------------------------------------------------------------<br />\nTonic Area: 1(do), 3(mi), 6(la)<br />\nDefining Sound: I-Maj7 in major key and I-MinMaj7 in minor keys</p>\n\n<p>Subdominant Area: 2(re), 4(fa), 6(la) - provides moderate progression<br />\nIV-Maj7 ~=&nbsp; II&ndash;7 ~= VI&ndash;7 in Major keys<br />\nIV7 ~= II&ndash;7 ~= VI&ndash;7(\u266d5)&nbsp; in Melodic Minor and Dorian<br />\nIV&ndash;7 ~= II&ndash;7(\u266d5) ~= \u266dVIMaj7 in Harmonic Minor</p>\n\n<p>Dominant Area: 5(sol) 7(ti)&nbsp; - provide strong forward progression - need to resolve<br />\nDefining Sound: V-7</p>\n\n<p>Secondary Dominant:<br />\nEvery key has a dominant, and every chord (except for diminished) has its own dominant called Secondary Dominant<br />\nVII chord located a 5th above the chord</p>\n\n<p>Voice-Leading:<br />\nSmooth movement (short jumps) b/w notes belonging to the chords</p>\n\n<p>Examples:<br />\nG(G-G-B-D) G-Maj7(G-F#-BD) G7(G-F-B-D) G6(G-E-B-D) G(b6)(G-Eb-B-D) G(G-D-B-D)</p>\n\n<p>Gm(G-G-Bb-D)</p>\n\n<hr />\n<h2>Key Signatures</h2>\n\n<p>Order of sharps: F&nbsp; &nbsp;C&nbsp; &nbsp;G&nbsp; &nbsp;D&nbsp; &nbsp;A&nbsp; &nbsp;E&nbsp; &nbsp;B</p>\n\n<p>Order of flats:&nbsp; &nbsp; B&nbsp; &nbsp;E&nbsp; &nbsp;A&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D&nbsp; &nbsp;G&nbsp; C&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;F</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The name of any flat key is the second last flat in key signature (F major has only one flat though).&nbsp;So, the key signatures based on number of sharps: B E A D G C.</p>\n\n<p>The name of sharp key is last sharp in key signature + 1 half-step (or semi-tone). So, the key signatures based on number of sharps: G D A E B F C</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>X -major is same as X#-major key except for C (because C has no sharp) and F (because F has only one flat).</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3>Time Signatures:</h3>\n\n<p>E.g. 3-4 time signature means 3 4-th (quartets) notes in one measure. The pieces normally would start with less than 3 (in the first measure) though! Anything that sums up to this number would work. Rests are also counted.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<ul>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.classicalguitarshed.com/free-guitar-sheet-music/\">Free Sheet/Tab Music</a>&nbsp;- <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q5l6piMQ6hw&amp;list=PLE32FpNcePwOTsp1DxBozAvdZX2xnkeoX&amp;index=1\" target=\"_blank\">Course Videos</a>,&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cTDhXdfeHZI&amp;list=PLS09nFAGbaWPuDpNlUtjTpW3b4Fo-hEO4\" target=\"_blank\">Robert Luhn</a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvsYImGb_6fpjfTxPK-I_Jg\" target=\"_blank\">Classical Guitar Corner</a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/dinatron/playlists\">Dinatron</a>/</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/SkyGuitar/playlists\">Sky Guitar</a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bICwAQM4Ox8&amp;list=PLm4o7oq_ivJRCOf9i0Tah90Ng1NR-i86y\">\u0425\u0438\u0442\u044b \u043d\u0430 \u0433\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0435</a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AcousticGuitarVideosLessons/playlists\" target=\"_blank\">Acoustic Fingerstyle</a></li>\n\t<li>Classical, Spanish etc, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Oa5PgIi64KI&amp;list=PLreN8RAd2yiZFDf30uArw0DnFkpfSVgto\">Playlist1</a>, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xk6M8vyf614&amp;list=PLreN8RAd2yia5YkFrE9oHMMkZ5gTEfruq&amp;index=5\">Playlist2</a>, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HBRlgFfE0EU&amp;list=PLreN8RAd2yiYjiU9h9I92wHDOIvA1ZQbw&amp;index=1\">3</a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/SixStringFingerpicking/playlists\">Six String Fingerpicking</a>, <a href=\"https://www.musicnotes.com/search/go?af=%20artist%3asix_string_fingerpicking&amp;lbc=musicnotes&amp;method=and&amp;p=Q&amp;uid=999643253&amp;w=*&amp;cnt=300\">tabs</a></li>\n\t<li>Yet another&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BpH3v-REUSQ&amp;list=PLMw5L_jRqXtOXrv4fR_Gv